<head>A.UD 412.4 / WINTER 2017 / <a href="https://descriptive.services/" target="_blank">G. FRIES-BRIGGS</a></head><br>
<figcaption>Course Description: Studio, 12 hours; outside study, six hours. Requisite: course 411. Concentration on basic skills, leading to projects exploring architectural program in relation to design process and, particularly, implications of program on architectural forms and concepts. In second phase, introduction of structural elements to fulfill program requirements and to support and further develop intended forms and concepts. <!--Letter grading.--> (From WINTER 2018 MyUCLA Class Detail Desc.) <a href="https://files.cargocollective.com/561384/2017---Winter---AUD-412---Syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">pdf</a></figcaption>
<h2><mark><b>"A Performing Library"</b></mark></h2>
<b>Duration:</b> 1 qtr (10 wks)
<b>Project:</b> Model Making, Architectural Drawings, Architectural Design
<b>Software:</b> Adobe Ai, Ps, Rhino 5
<b>Shop Media:</b> Laser-Cut, 3D Powder Print.
<p>This studio investigated material designs and interplay to be used to develop a Library Design in the Western end of Bunker Hill.</p>
<p><b>Precedent: The Musashino Arts Library, Sou Fujimoto</b>
<br style="line-height: 10px">{image 37}</p>
<figcaption><i>An online image of the Musashino Arts Library, in Musashino, Japan; designed by Sou Fujimoto.</i></figcaption>
<p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E6%AD%A6%E8%94%B5%E9%87%8E%E7%BE%8E%E8%A1%93%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6+%E5%9B%B3%E6%9B%B8%E9%A4%A8/@35.7280273,139.4451581,173a,35y,138.98h,47.26t/data=!3m1!1e3!4m12!1m6!3m5!1s0x6018e6cb125391c7:0xe245216965837f7d!2sMusashino+Art+University+Takanodai+Campus!8m2!3d35.7261896!4d139.447649!3m4!1s0x0:0xc533b28cc0fc20b1!8m2!3d35.7265042!4d139.446252" target="_blank">The Musashino Arts Library</a> employs a winding double-height book stacks / wall to uphold a light steel frame roofing system and a 2nd Floor catwalk circulating across parts of the wooden structural stacks system.</p>
{image 36}
<figcaption><i>"Horiz-Axon" Sally Chae (2018)</i></figcaption>
<p>The horizontal exploded axonometric drawing of the Musashino Arts Library shows the passage of elements along a central, winding circulation path.</p>
{image 24}
<figcaption><i>"Chunk-Axon" Sally Chae (2018)</i></figcaption>
<p>The select exploded axon identifies the materials, construction and effective employment of the Library's principle at the core of the winding circulatory path.</p>
